09/08/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- An elderly Serb couple, Bogdan and Trajanka Petkovic, were found dead in their house in the village of Partes near Gnjilane, regional police spokesperson Remzi Azemi announced on Friday (August 7th). Azemi did not reveal any details about the incident but said an investigation is underway. The Kosovo police said on Saturday there are no indications that the crime was ethnically motivated. Partes is one of the biggest Serb-dominated villages in Kosovo and is the home of around 300 families. (B92, Beta - 08/08/09; FoNet, Beta, Tanjug, B92, BTA - 07/08/09)
